- Google Finance price fetch: use fetch() to 
  https://www.google.com/finance/quote/RELIANCE:NSE and parse the price from the page,
  OR fallback to showing a manual "Enter current price" input with a "Fetch" button
  that opens Google Finance in a new tab for the user to reference
- All new forms must follow existing security.js sanitization patterns
- Reuse existing styles from src/styles/index.js — extend don't replace
- All new components go in src/components/ with descriptive names
- All new pages go in src/pages/
- Update src/constants/index.js with any new enums (asset sub-types, goal templates etc.)
- Maintain the liquid-glass visual aesthetic: backdrop-filter blur, 
  rgba backgrounds, shimmer borders on all new cards/modals
- All charts use Recharts — maintain existing chart styling patterns
- Keep mobile responsiveness intact
- For live price fetching, add a global PriceService in src/services/priceService.js
  that caches prices for 15 minutes in sessionStorage to avoid excessive requests